The paper deals with fingerprint image enhancement, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. The proposed algorithm uses fuzzy c-means clustering for quality assessment, which is a common technique in machine learning and pattern recognition (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of Gabor filtering, which is a common technique in image processing and computer vision (cs.IR). The use of short term Fourier transform and oriented diffusion filtering also suggests the paper may belong to cs.MM. The paper also discusses the improvement in verification results, which suggests it may belong to cs.CR. Finally, the use of adaptive preprocessing and enhancement techniques suggests the paper may belong to cs.LG.
